<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Two integers are represented by <m>x</m> and <m> (x + {21}) </m>. Form and simplify an expression for their product.
</p>
<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The two numbers are:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x \quad \text{and} \quad x + {21}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Their product is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x(x + {21})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Multiply <m>x</m> by both terms in the bracket:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x \cdot x + x \cdot {21} = x^2 + {21}x
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the simplified product is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{x^2 + {21}x}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2+21 x</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>